reviews.review_text: Flipped It sounds like left and right are flipped on this source.  The cassette source seems to sound better.

disagree This is a true soundboard source of this excellent show. It seems to me that it is not as smoothed out as the Walker- Scotton tape but it is sonically much stronger and truer to the original show sound in my opinion and yes i do think think both Phil and Jerry were coming out of the left channel most of the time at this show but listen to Brent go nuts in his playground on the right soooo... and it sounds great...Damn they just jam the shit out of every song and very well too. Still gets 5 stars from me soundwarts and all.

saint of huh everyone is on a different page

love the 89 A.getaway
bizarre mix something is wrong here. not gonna take time to figure out what. it sounds wrong. Very strong show though, check the other Miller source

Memorable Was there for this show with some CA friends - Hello Andrea, wherever you are - and was on my feet for the whole show.  John Cipollina had died a few days earlier and some of us expected a killer He's Gone.  Jerry did not fail us.  Could hear him mourning as the song wound on.

I play this often to remember the good times and friends gone by.

Great show and the last one for me This was the last concert I got to see before I moved out of California, man I miss it. Fantastic show of course and the mall is always fun. I didn't get to go to any more Deadshows after that.
